caption: I loved this place, a lot of shadowy spots, pretty plants and nice views. Btw the movie 'Before Sunset' was filmed here.
Lovely use of abandoned train tracks.  Very well maintained gardens stretching across Paris.  Provides a different view than street level.  Generally not as crowded as the streets below.
Really lovely walk
Very quiet and pretty place, I love it!
Loverly plants and a nice walk
Hidden gem. Free. Wonderful.  Seated. Peaceful.
Start of a lovely walk with plenty of shade and different areas and parks to walk through.

Starts around the Bastille area and heads south east for about 5km. Known as the “green corridor” to Parisians, it’s an amazing green and relaxing space above the busy avenues of Paris. Very jealous of the apartments looking over the highline park. Very cool.
Lovely walk with footage and flowers.  The ducks in the water feature are cute.  In May the iris were blooming and the colors were magnificent.  Many roses plsnted
Beautiful park. The model for NYC's Highline. A delightful walk.
This is a staircase up to the "corridor plantee" or the Coulee Verte Renee-Dumont (look it up on Maps), which is a raised walkway lined with greenery. Very nice for a stroll.
Beautiful green walk a bit above Paris streets. Look at the flowers, look at all the people and breathe for a while
Amazing place
Beautiful walk.
Great place ,Suit for running and relax
Sweet secluded spot in the busy city.
Nice for a walk
Green oasis!

It's a place that took me a little while to find, but once I did, it was a surprise Typical place to walk quietly, sit, talk to someone, take photos... especially see Paris from above I went up some stairs that I found, since the location is not very well placed And it is a straight passage in which you see Paris from above Yes, it is true that if you want to go down, from one staircase to another it takes quite a while.

Everyone knows the High Line in New York. This is the little brother in Paris. Situated high on an old railway line where trains used to run. You look out over the streets, look inside the Parisian apartments and walk between greenery and from Canal St Martin to 2 parks; Don't forget parque de Bercy.
Taemin, Will I Hug You? The exact same place in the MV! It seemed like a jogging place for locals, so I just quietly took pictures.
Very nice walk.
Very pleasant to walk among the trees in the heart of Paris! Great discovery to make when the weather is nice
Excellent for a quiet walk in the middle of Paris
A little New York flair in Paris Very nice discovery!!
Nice to get some fresh air
